      "content": "I understand your concern, but I would strongly advise against taking an extra insulin shot without checking your levels first. Taking insulin without properly assessing your blood sugar can indeed cause a spike, and since you're already feeling lightheaded, it's even more critical to wait and get a accurate reading. Wait for at least 15-30 minutes, and consider checking your levels with your continuous glucose monitor or a quick test strip to get an accurate reading before taking any action.",
